AUDIO: 'enormous, and you might have a lot of different lines here that, if you try to scrape everything just by going for a simpler scraper, what happens is that you\'re tokenizing everything. This will'

[05:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'take a longer time to be processed. This will waste you more money because of this tokenization. Your model can hallucinate because of this, and you can eventually reach the context window much, much faster and have to wait for that context window to be compressed'

[05:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'just to only continue. And while that\'s being compressed, you\'re wasting more money, more time, and the ongoing infinite context window loop. Now, what happens when you\'re using the Firecrawl CLI is the following. Whenever the agent needs to scrape, it goes over to that'

[05:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'website, grabs everything, and instead of adding it to the context window, it actually saves that in the file system, which is this exact huge markdown right here. And then, whenever it needs to'

[05:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'read this file, it has a lot of different tools to do that. That is in fact exactly what Claude Code is specialized in doing because it is designed to deal with huge code bases. So, for example, it has the access to tools like a finder where it could add a'

